  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: "1: The Report of Saul\u2019s Death"
      title: "The Report of Saul\u2019s Death"
      number: 1
      content: 'Now it came to pass after the death of Saul, when David had returned
        from the slaughter of the Amalekites, and David had stayed two days in Ziklag, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "on the third day, behold, it happened that a man came from Saul\u2019s
        camp with his clothes torn and dust on his head. So it was, when he came
        to David, that he fell to the ground and prostrated himself."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And David said to him, \u201CWhere have you come from?\u201DSo he
        said to him, \u201CI have escaped from the camp of Israel.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then David said to him, \u201CHow did the matter go? Please tell
        me.\u201DAnd he answered, \u201CThe people have fled from the battle, many
        of the people are fallen and dead, and Saul and Jonathan his son are dead
        also.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "So David said to the young man who told him, \u201CHow do you know
        that Saul and Jonathan his son are dead?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then the young man who told him said, \u201CAs I happened by chance
        to  be on Mount Gilboa, there was Saul, leaning on his spear; and indeed
        the chariots and horsemen followed hard after him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Now when he looked behind him, he saw me and called to me. And I
        answered, \u2018Here I am.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And he said to me, \u2018Who are you?\u2019 So I answered him, \u2018I
        am an Amalekite.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "He said to me again, \u2018Please stand over me and kill me, for
        anguish has come upon me, but my life still remains in me.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "So I stood over him and killed him, because I was sure that he could
        not live after he had fallen. And I took the crown that was on his head and
        the bracelet that was on his arm, and have brought them here to my lord.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Therefore David took hold of his own clothes and tore them, and so 
        did all the men who were with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: And they mourned and wept and fasted until evening for Saul and for
        Jonathan his son, for the people of the Lord and for the house of Israel,
        because they had fallen by the sword.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then David said to the young man who told him, \u201CWhere are you
        from?\u201DAnd he answered, \u201CI am the son of an alien, an Amalekite.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "So David said to him, \u201CHow was it you were not afraid to put
        forth your hand to destroy the Lord\u2019s anointed?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then David called one of the young men and said, \u201CGo near, and
        execute him!\u201D And he struck him so that he died. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: The Song of the Bow'
      title: The Song of the Bow
      number: 16
      content: "So David said to him, \u201CYour blood is on your own head, for your
        own mouth has testified against you, saying, \u2018I have killed the Lord\u2019s
        anointed.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then David lamented with this lamentation over Saul and over Jonathan
        his son, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'and he told them to teach the children of Judah the  Song  of the
        Bow; indeed it  is written in the Book of Jasher:'
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CThe beauty of Israel is slain on your high places!How the mighty
        have fallen!"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Tell it not in Gath,Proclaim it not in the streets of Ashkelon\u2014Lest
        the daughters of the Philistines rejoice,Lest the daughters of the uncircumcised
        triumph."
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CO mountains of Gilboa,Let  there  be no dew nor rain upon you,Nor
        fields of offerings.For the shield of the mighty is cast away there!The shield
        of Saul, not anointed with oil."
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: From the blood of the slain,From the fat of the mighty,The bow of
        Jonathan did not turn back,And the sword of Saul did not return empty.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CSaul and Jonathan were beloved and pleasant in their lives,And
        in their death they were not divided;They were swifter than eagles,They were
        stronger than lions."
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CO daughters of Israel, weep over Saul,Who clothed you in scarlet,
        with luxury;Who put ornaments of gold on your apparel."
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CHow the mighty have fallen in the midst of the battle!Jonathan
        was slain in your high places."
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: I am distressed for you, my brother Jonathan;You have been very pleasant
        to me;Your love to me was wonderful,Surpassing the love of women.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CHow the mighty have fallen,And the weapons of war perished!\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David Anointed King of Judah'
      title: David Anointed King of Judah
      number: 1
      content: "It happened after this that David inquired of the Lord, saying, \u201CShall
        I go up to any of the cities of Judah?\u201DAnd the Lord said to him, \u201CGo
        up.\u201DDavid said, \u201CWhere shall I go up?\u201DAnd He said, \u201CTo
        Hebron.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So David went up there, and his two wives also, Ahinoam the Jezreelitess,
        and Abigail the widow of Nabal the Carmelite. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: And David brought up the men who were with him, every man with his
        household. So they dwelt in the cities of Hebron.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then the men of Judah came, and there they anointed David king over
        the house of Judah. And they told David, saying, \u201CThe men of Jabesh
        Gilead were  the  ones who buried Saul.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "So David sent messengers to the men of Jabesh Gilead, and said to
        them, \u201CYou are blessed of the Lord, for you have shown this kindness
        to your lord, to Saul, and have buried him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And now may the Lord show kindness and truth to you. I also will
        repay you this kindness, because you have done this thing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: Ishbosheth Made King of Israel'
      title: Ishbosheth Made King of Israel
      number: 7
      content: "Now therefore, let your hands be strengthened, and be valiant; for
        your master Saul is dead, and also the house of Judah has anointed me king
        over them.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "But Abner the son of Ner, commander of Saul\u2019s army, took Ishbosheth
        the son of Saul and brought him over to Mahanaim; "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'and he made him king over Gilead, over the Ashurites, over Jezreel,
        over Ephraim, over Benjamin, and over all Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Ishbosheth, Saul\u2019s son, was forty years old when he began to
        reign over Israel, and he reigned two years. Only the house of Judah followed
        David. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: Israel and Judah at War'
      title: Israel and Judah at War
      number: 11
      content: And the time that David was king in Hebron over the house of Judah
        was seven years and six months.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Now Abner the son of Ner, and the servants of Ishbosheth the son
        of Saul, went out from Mahanaim to Gibeon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And Joab the son of Zeruiah, and the servants of David, went out
        and met them by the pool of Gibeon. So they sat down, one on one side of
        the pool and the other on the other side of the pool. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then Abner said to Joab, \u201CLet the young men now arise and compete
        before us.\u201DAnd Joab said, \u201CLet them arise.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So they arose and went over by number, twelve from Benjamin, followers
        of Ishbosheth the son of Saul, and twelve from the servants of David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And each one grasped his opponent by the head and thrust his sword
        in his opponent\u2019s side; so they fell down together. Therefore that place
        was called the Field of Sharp Swords, which is in Gibeon. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: So there was a very fierce battle that day, and Abner and the men
        of Israel were beaten before the servants of David.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Now the three sons of Zeruiah were there: Joab and Abishai and Asahel.
        And Asahel was  as fleet of foot as a wild gazelle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: So Asahel pursued Abner, and in going he did not turn to the right
        hand or to the left from following Abner.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then Abner looked behind him and said, \u201CAre you Asahel?\u201DHe
        answered, \u201CI am.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And Abner said to him, \u201CTurn aside to your right hand or to
        your left, and lay hold on one of the young men and take his armor for yourself.\u201D
        But Asahel would not turn aside from following him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "So Abner said again to Asahel, \u201CTurn aside from following me.
        Why should I strike you to the ground? How then could I face your brother
        Joab?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: However, he refused to turn aside. Therefore Abner struck him in the
        stomach with the blunt end of the spear, so that the spear came out of his
        back; and he fell down there and died on the spot. So it was that as many
        as came to the place where Asahel fell down and died, stood still.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Joab and Abishai also pursued Abner. And the sun was going down when
        they came to the hill of Ammah, which is before Giah by the road to the Wilderness
        of Gibeon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Now the children of Benjamin gathered together behind Abner and became
        a unit, and took their stand on top of a hill. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Then Abner called to Joab and said, \u201CShall the sword devour
        forever? Do you not know that it will be bitter in the latter end? How long
        will it be then until you tell the people to return from pursuing their brethren?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "And Joab said, \u201CAs God lives, unless you had spoken, surely
        then by morning all the people would have given up pursuing their brethren.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'So Joab blew a trumpet; and all the people stood still and did not
        pursue Israel anymore, nor did they fight anymore. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: Then Abner and his men went on all that night through the plain, crossed
        over the Jordan, and went through all Bithron; and they came to Mahanaim.
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "So Joab returned from pursuing Abner. And when he had gathered all
        the people together, there were missing of David\u2019s servants nineteen
        men and Asahel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "But the servants of David had struck down, of Benjamin and Abner\u2019s
        men, three hundred and sixty men who died. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Then they took up Asahel and buried him in his father\u2019s tomb,
        which was  in  Bethlehem. And Joab and his men went all night, and they came
        to Hebron at daybreak."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Sons of David'
      title: Sons of David
      number: 1
      content: Now there was a long war between the house of Saul and the house of
        David. But David grew stronger and stronger, and the house of Saul grew weaker
        and weaker.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Sons were born to David in Hebron: His firstborn was Amnon by Ahinoam
        the Jezreelitess; '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'his second, Chileab, by Abigail the widow of Nabal the Carmelite;
        the third, Absalom the son of Maacah, the daughter of Talmai, king of Geshur; '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'the fourth, Adonijah the son of Haggith; the fifth, Shephatiah the
        son of Abital; '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: Abner Joins Forces with David'
      title: Abner Joins Forces with David
      number: 5
      content: "and the sixth, Ithream, by David\u2019s wife Eglah. These were born
        to David in Hebron."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Now it was so, while there was war between the house of Saul and the
        house of David, that Abner was strengthening his  hold on the house of Saul.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And Saul had a concubine, whose name was  Rizpah, the daughter of
        Aiah. So Ishbosheth said to Abner, \u201CWhy have you gone in to my father\u2019s
        concubine?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then Abner became very angry at the words of Ishbosheth, and said,
        \u201CAm I a dog\u2019s head that belongs to Judah? Today I show loyalty
        to the house of Saul your father, to his brothers, and to his friends, and
        have not delivered you into the hand of David; and you charge me today with
        a fault concerning this woman? "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "May God do so to Abner, and more also, if I do not do for David as
        the Lord has sworn to him\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "to transfer the kingdom from the house of Saul, and set up the throne
        of David over Israel and over Judah, from Dan to Beersheba.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: And he could not answer Abner another word, because he feared him.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then Abner sent messengers on his behalf to David, saying, \u201CWhose
        is the land?\u201D saying also, \u201CMake your covenant with me, and indeed
        my hand shall  be with you to bring all Israel to you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And David said, \u201CGood, I will make a covenant with you. But
        one thing I require of you: you shall not see my face unless you first bring
        Michal, Saul\u2019s daughter, when you come to see my face.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "So David sent messengers to Ishbosheth, Saul\u2019s son, saying,
        \u201CGive me my wife Michal, whom I betrothed to myself for a hundred foreskins
        of the Philistines.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And Ishbosheth sent and took her from her husband, from Paltiel the
        son of Laish. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then her husband went along with her to Bahurim, weeping behind her.
        So Abner said to him, \u201CGo, return!\u201D And he returned."
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Now Abner had communicated with the elders of Israel, saying, \u201CIn
        time past you were seeking for David to  be king over you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Now then, do it!  For the Lord has spoken of David, saying, \u2018By
        the hand of My servant David, I will save My people Israel from the hand
        of the Philistines and the hand of all their enemies.\u2019 \u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: And Abner also spoke in the hearing of Benjamin. Then Abner also went
        to speak in the hearing of David in Hebron all that seemed good to Israel
        and the whole house of Benjamin.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'So Abner and twenty men with him came to David at Hebron. And David
        made a feast for Abner and the men who were with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: Joab Murders Abner'
      title: Joab Murders Abner
      number: 21
      content: "Then Abner said to David, \u201CI will arise and go, and gather all
        Israel to my lord the king, that they may make a covenant with you, and that
        you may reign over all that your heart desires.\u201D So David sent Abner
        away, and he went in peace."
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'At that moment the servants of David and Joab came from a raid and
        brought much spoil with them. But Abner was not with David in Hebron, for
        he had sent him away, and he had gone in peace. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "When Joab and all the troops that were with him had come, they told
        Joab, saying, \u201CAbner the son of Ner came to the king, and he sent him
        away, and he has gone in peace.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Then Joab came to the king and said, \u201CWhat have you done? Look,
        Abner came to you; why is it that you sent him away, and he has already gone? "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Surely you realize that Abner the son of Ner came to deceive you,
        to know your going out and your coming in, and to know all that you are doing.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "And when Joab had gone from David\u2019s presence, he sent messengers
        after Abner, who brought him back from the well of Sirah. But David did not
        know it.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: Now when Abner had returned to Hebron, Joab took him aside in the
        gate to speak with him privately, and there stabbed him in the stomach, so
        that he died for the blood of Asahel his brother.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Afterward, when David heard it, he said, \u201CMy kingdom and I are
        guiltless before the Lord forever of the blood of Abner the son of Ner. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Let it rest on the head of Joab and on all his father\u2019s house;
        and let there never fail to be in the house of Joab one who has a discharge
        or is a leper, who leans on a staff or falls by the sword, or who lacks bread.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "30: David\u2019s Mourning for Abner"
      title: "David\u2019s Mourning for Abner"
      number: 30
      content: So Joab and Abishai his brother killed Abner, because he had killed
        their brother Asahel at Gibeon in the battle.
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Then David said to Joab and to all the people who were with him,
        \u201CTear your clothes, gird yourselves with sackcloth, and mourn for Abner.\u201D
        And King David followed the coffin. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'So they buried Abner in Hebron; and the king lifted up his voice
        and wept at the grave of Abner, and all the people wept. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "And the king sang a  lament over Abner and said:\u201CShould Abner
        die as a fool dies?"
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Your hands were not boundNor your feet put into fetters;As a man
        falls before wicked men, so you fell.\u201DThen all the people wept over
        him again."
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "And when all the people came to persuade David to eat food while
        it was still day, David took an oath, saying, \u201CGod do so to me, and
        more also, if I taste bread or anything else till the sun goes down!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Now all the people took note of  it, and it pleased them, since whatever
        the king did pleased all the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "For all the people and all Israel understood that day that it had
        not been the king\u2019s intent to kill Abner the son of Ner. "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "Then the king said to his servants, \u201CDo you not know that a
        prince and a great man has fallen this day in Israel? "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "And I am weak today, though anointed king; and these men, the sons
        of Zeruiah, are too harsh for me. The Lord shall repay the evildoer according
        to his wickedness.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Ishbosheth Is Murdered'
      title: Ishbosheth Is Murdered
      number: 1
      content: "When Saul\u2019s son heard that Abner had died in Hebron, he lost
        heart, and all Israel was troubled. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Now Saul\u2019s son had two men who  were captains of troops. The
        name of one was Baanah and the name of the other Rechab, the sons of Rimmon
        the Beerothite, of the children of Benjamin. (For Beeroth also was part of
        Benjamin, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: because the Beerothites fled to Gittaim and have been sojourners there
        until this day.)
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Jonathan, Saul\u2019s son, had a son who  was lame in his feet. He
        was five years old when the news about Saul and Jonathan came from Jezreel;
        and his nurse took him up and fled. And it happened, as she made haste to
        flee, that he fell and became lame. His name was  Mephibosheth."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then the sons of Rimmon the Beerothite, Rechab and Baanah, set out
        and came at about the heat of the day to the house of Ishbosheth, who was
        lying on his bed at noon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And they came there, all the way into the house, as  though to get
        wheat, and they stabbed him in the stomach. Then Rechab and Baanah his brother
        escaped. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For when they came into the house, he was lying on his bed in his
        bedroom; then they struck him and killed him, beheaded him and took his head,
        and were all night escaping through the plain. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And they brought the head of Ishbosheth to David at Hebron, and said
        to the king, \u201CHere is the head of Ishbosheth, the son of Saul your enemy,
        who sought your life; and the Lord has avenged my lord the king this day
        of Saul and his descendants.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "But David answered Rechab and Baanah his brother, the sons of Rimmon
        the Beerothite, and said to them, \u201CAs the Lord lives, who has redeemed
        my life from all adversity, "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "when someone told me, saying, \u2018Look, Saul is dead,\u2019 thinking
        to have brought good news, I arrested him and had him executed in Ziklag\u2014the
        one who thought I would give him a reward for his news. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "How much more, when wicked men have killed a righteous person in
        his own house on his bed? Therefore, shall I not now require his blood at
        your hand and remove you from the earth?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: So David commanded his young men, and they executed them, cut off
        their hands and feet, and hanged them by the pool in Hebron. But they took
        the head of Ishbosheth and buried it in the tomb of Abner in Hebron.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David Reigns over All Israel'
      title: David Reigns over All Israel
      number: 1
      content: "Then all the tribes of Israel came to David at Hebron and spoke,
        saying, \u201CIndeed we are your bone and your flesh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Also, in time past, when Saul was king over us, you were the one
        who led Israel out and brought them in; and the Lord said to you, \u2018You
        shall shepherd My people Israel, and be ruler over Israel.\u2019 \u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Therefore all the elders of Israel came to the king at Hebron, and
        King David made a covenant with them at Hebron before the Lord. And they
        anointed David king over Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'David was  thirty years old when he began to reign, and  he reigned
        forty years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: The Conquest of Jerusalem'
      title: The Conquest of Jerusalem
      number: 5
      content: In Hebron he reigned over Judah seven years and six months, and in
        Jerusalem he reigned thirty-three years over all Israel and Judah.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And the king and his men went to Jerusalem against the Jebusites,
        the inhabitants of the land, who spoke to David, saying, \u201CYou shall
        not come in here; but the blind and the lame will repel you,\u201D thinking,
        \u201CDavid cannot come in here.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Nevertheless David took the stronghold of Zion (that is, the City
        of David).
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Now David said on that day, \u201CWhoever climbs up by way of the
        water shaft and defeats the Jebusites (the lame and the blind, who  are hated
        by David\u2019s soul), he  shall  be  chief  and  captain.\u201D Therefore
        they say, \u201CThe blind and the lame shall not come into the house.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then David dwelt in the stronghold, and called it the City of David.
        And David built all around from the Millo and inward. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: So David went on and became great, and the Lord God of hosts was with
        him.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then Hiram king of Tyre sent messengers to David, and cedar trees,
        and carpenters and masons. And they built David a house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: So David knew that the Lord had established him as king over Israel,
        and that He had exalted His kingdom for the sake of His people Israel.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And David took more concubines and wives from Jerusalem, after he
        had come from Hebron. Also more sons and daughters were born to David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Now these are the names of those who were born to him in Jerusalem:
        Shammua, Shobab, Nathan, Solomon, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Ibhar, Elishua, Nepheg, Japhia, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: The Philistines Defeated'
      title: The Philistines Defeated
      number: 16
      content: Elishama, Eliada, and Eliphelet.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Now when the Philistines heard that they had anointed David king
        over Israel, all the Philistines went up to search for David. And David heard
        of  it  and went down to the stronghold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The Philistines also went and deployed themselves in the Valley of
        Rephaim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "So David inquired of the Lord, saying, \u201CShall I go up against
        the Philistines? Will You deliver them into my hand?\u201DAnd the Lord said
        to David, \u201CGo up, for I will doubtless deliver the Philistines into
        your hand.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "So David went to Baal Perazim, and David defeated them there; and
        he said, \u201CThe Lord has broken through my enemies before me, like a breakthrough
        of water.\u201D Therefore he called the name of that place Baal Perazim. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: And they left their images there, and David and his men carried them
        away.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Then the Philistines went up once again and deployed themselves in
        the Valley of Rephaim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Therefore David inquired of the Lord, and He said, \u201CYou shall
        not go up; circle around behind them, and come upon them in front of the
        mulberry trees. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And it shall be, when you hear the sound of marching in the tops
        of the mulberry trees, then you shall advance quickly. For then the Lord
        will go out before you to strike the camp of the Philistines.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: And David did so, as the Lord commanded him; and he drove back the
        Philistines from Geba as far as Gezer.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Ark Brought to Jerusalem'
      title: The Ark Brought to Jerusalem
      number: 1
      content: 'Again David gathered all the choice men of Israel, thirty thousand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And David arose and went with all the people who were with him from
        Baale Judah to bring up from there the ark of God, whose name is called by
        the Name, the Lord of Hosts, who dwells between the cherubim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So they set the ark of God on a new cart, and brought it out of the
        house of Abinadab, which was on the hill; and Uzzah and Ahio, the sons of
        Abinadab, drove the new cart. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And they brought it out of the house of Abinadab, which was on the
        hill, accompanying the ark of God; and Ahio went before the ark. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Then David and all the house of Israel played music before the Lord
        on all kinds of instruments  of fir wood, on harps, on stringed instruments,
        on tambourines, on sistrums, and on cymbals.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And when they came to Nachon\u2019s threshing floor, Uzzah put out
        his  hand to the ark of God and took hold of it, for the oxen stumbled. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Then the anger of the Lord was aroused against Uzzah, and God struck
        him there for his error; and he died there by the ark of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And David became angry because of the Lord\u2019s outbreak against
        Uzzah; and he called the name of the place Perez Uzzah to this day."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "David was afraid of the Lord that day; and he said, \u201CHow can
        the ark of the Lord come to me?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'So David would not move the ark of the Lord with him into the City
        of David; but David took it aside into the house of Obed-Edom the Gittite. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: The ark of the Lord remained in the house of Obed-Edom the Gittite
        three months. And the Lord  blessed Obed-Edom and all his household.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Now it was told King David, saying, \u201CThe Lord has blessed the
        house of Obed-Edom and all that belongs to him, because of the ark of God.\u201D
        So David went and brought up the ark of God from the house of Obed-Edom to
        the City of David with gladness. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And so it was, when those bearing the ark of the Lord had gone six
        paces, that he sacrificed oxen and fatted sheep. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Then David danced before the Lord with all his might; and David was
        wearing a linen ephod. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: So David and all the house of Israel brought up the ark of the Lord
        with shouting and with the sound of the trumpet.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Now as the ark of the Lord came into the City of David, Michal, Saul\u2019s
        daughter, looked through a window and saw King David leaping and whirling
        before the Lord; and she despised him in her heart. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'So they brought the ark of the Lord, and set it in its place in the
        midst of the tabernacle that David had erected for it. Then David offered
        burnt offerings and peace offerings before the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And when David had finished offering burnt offerings and peace offerings,
        he blessed the people in the name of the Lord of hosts. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: Then he distributed among all the people, among the whole multitude
        of Israel, both the women and the men, to everyone a loaf of bread, a piece
        of  meat, and a cake of raisins. So all the people departed, everyone to
        his house.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then David returned to bless his household. And Michal the daughter
        of Saul came out to meet David, and said, \u201CHow glorious was the king
        of Israel today, uncovering himself today in the eyes of the maids of his
        servants, as one of the base fellows shamelessly uncovers himself!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "So David said to Michal, \u201CIt  was before the Lord, who chose
        me instead of your father and all his house, to appoint me ruler over the
        people of the Lord, over Israel. Therefore I will play music before the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And I will be even more undignified than this, and will be humble
        in my own sight. But as for the maidservants of whom you have spoken, by
        them I will be held in honor.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: Therefore Michal the daughter of Saul had no children to the day of
        her death.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: God\u2019s Covenant with David"
      title: "God\u2019s Covenant with David"
      number: 1
      content: 'Now it came to pass when the king was dwelling in his house, and
        the Lord had given him rest from all his enemies all around, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "that the king said to Nathan the prophet, \u201CSee now, I dwell
        in a house of cedar, but the ark of God dwells inside tent curtains.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then Nathan said to the king, \u201CGo, do all that is in your heart,
        for the Lord  is with you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But it happened that night that the word of the Lord came to Nathan,
        saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CGo and tell My servant David, \u2018Thus says the Lord: \u201CWould
        you build a house for Me to dwell in? "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For I have not dwelt in a house since the time that I brought the
        children of Israel up from Egypt, even to this day, but have moved about
        in a tent and in a tabernacle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Wherever I have moved about with all the children of Israel, have
        I ever spoken a word to anyone from the tribes of Israel, whom I commanded
        to shepherd My people Israel, saying, \u2018Why have you not built Me a house
        of cedar?\u2019 \u201D \u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Now therefore, thus shall you say to My servant David, \u2018Thus
        says the Lord of hosts: \u201CI took you from the sheepfold, from following
        the sheep, to be ruler over My people, over Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And I have been with you wherever you have gone, and have cut off
        all your enemies from before you, and have made you a great name, like the
        name of the great men who are on the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Moreover I will appoint a place for My people Israel, and will plant
        them, that they may dwell in a place of their own and move no more; nor shall
        the sons of wickedness oppress them anymore, as previously, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: since the time that I commanded judges to  be over My people Israel,
        and have caused you to rest from all your enemies. Also the Lord tells you
        that He will make you a house.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CWhen your days are fulfilled and you rest with your fathers,
        I will set up your seed after you, who will come from your body, and I will
        establish his kingdom. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'He shall build a house for My name, and I will establish the throne
        of his kingdom forever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'I will be his Father, and he shall be My son. If he commits iniquity,
        I will chasten him with the rod of men and with the blows of the sons of
        men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'But My mercy shall not depart from him, as I took it from Saul, whom
        I removed from before you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And your house and your kingdom shall be established forever before
        you. Your throne shall be established forever.\u201D \u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: "17: David\u2019s Thanksgiving to God"
      title: "David\u2019s Thanksgiving to God"
      number: 17
      content: According to all these words and according to all this vision, so
        Nathan spoke to David.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then King David went in and sat before the Lord; and he said: \u201CWho
        am I, O Lord God? And what is my house, that You have brought me this far? "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And yet this was a small thing in Your sight, O Lord God; and You
        have also spoken of Your servant\u2019s house for a great while to come.
        Is this the manner of man, O Lord God? "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Now what more can David say to You? For You, Lord God, know Your
        servant. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "For Your word\u2019s sake, and according to Your own heart, You have
        done all these great things, to make Your servant know them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Therefore You are great, O Lord God. For there  is none like You,
        nor is  there  any God besides You, according to all that we have heard with
        our ears. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And who is like Your people, like Israel, the one nation on the earth
        whom God went to redeem for Himself as a people, to make for Himself a name\u2014and
        to do for Yourself great and awesome deeds for Your land\u2014before Your
        people whom You redeemed for Yourself from Egypt, the nations, and their
        gods? "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: For You have made Your people Israel Your very own people forever;
        and You, Lord, have become their God.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CNow, O Lord God, the word which You have spoken concerning
        Your servant and concerning his house, establish it forever and do as You
        have said. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "So let Your name be magnified forever, saying, \u2018The Lord of
        hosts is the God over Israel.\u2019 And let the house of Your servant David
        be established before You. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "For You, O Lord of hosts, God of Israel, have revealed this to Your
        servant, saying, \u2018I will build you a house.\u2019 Therefore Your servant
        has found it in his heart to pray this prayer to You."
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "\u201CAnd now, O Lord God, You are God, and Your words are true,
        and You have promised this goodness to Your servant. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Now therefore, let it please You to bless the house of Your servant,
        that it may continue before You forever; for You, O Lord God, have spoken
        it, and with Your blessing let the house of Your servant be blessed forever.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: David\u2019s Further Conquests"
      title: "David\u2019s Further Conquests"
      number: 1
      content: After this it came to pass that David attacked the Philistines and
        subdued them. And David took Metheg Ammah from the hand of the Philistines.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Then he defeated Moab. Forcing them down to the ground, he measured
        them off with a line. With two lines he measured off those to be put to death,
        and with one full line those to be kept alive. So the Moabites became David\u2019s
        servants, and  brought tribute."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'David also defeated Hadadezer the son of Rehob, king of Zobah, as
        he went to recover his territory at the River Euphrates. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: David took from him one thousand chariots, seven hundred horsemen,
        and twenty thousand foot soldiers. Also David hamstrung all the chariot horses,
        except that he spared enough of them for one hundred chariots.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'When the Syrians of Damascus came to help Hadadezer king of Zobah,
        David killed twenty-two thousand of the Syrians. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then David put garrisons in Syria of Damascus; and the Syrians became
        David\u2019s servants, and brought tribute. So the Lord preserved David wherever
        he went. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And David took the shields of gold that had belonged to the servants
        of Hadadezer, and brought them to Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Also from Betah and from Berothai, cities of Hadadezer, King David
        took a large amount of bronze.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'When Toi king of Hamath heard that David had defeated all the army
        of Hadadezer, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'then Toi sent Joram his son to King David, to greet him and bless
        him, because he had fought against Hadadezer and defeated him (for Hadadezer
        had been at war with Toi); and Joram brought with him articles of silver,
        articles of gold, and articles of bronze. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "King David also dedicated these to the Lord, along with the silver
        and gold that he had dedicated from all the nations which he had subdued\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: from Syria, from Moab, from the people of Ammon, from the Philistines,
        from Amalek, and from the spoil of Hadadezer the son of Rehob, king of Zobah.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And David made himself a name when he returned from killing eighteen
        thousand Syrians in the Valley of Salt. '
      comments: []
    - name: "14: David\u2019s Administration"
      title: "David\u2019s Administration"
      number: 14
      content: "He also put garrisons in Edom; throughout all Edom he put garrisons,
        and all the Edomites became David\u2019s servants. And the Lord preserved
        David wherever he went."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So David reigned over all Israel; and David administered judgment
        and justice to all his people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Joab the son of Zeruiah was over the army; Jehoshaphat the son of
        Ahilud was recorder; '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Zadok the son of Ahitub and Ahimelech the son of Abiathar were the
        priests; Seraiah was the scribe; '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Benaiah the son of Jehoiada was  over both the Cherethites and the
        Pelethites; and David\u2019s sons were chief ministers."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: David\u2019s Kindness to Mephibosheth"
      title: "David\u2019s Kindness to Mephibosheth"
      number: 1
      content: "Now David said, \u201CIs there still anyone who is left of the house
        of Saul, that I may show him kindness for Jonathan\u2019s sake?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And there  was a servant of the house of Saul whose name was  Ziba.
        So when they had called him to David, the king said to him, \u201CAre you
        Ziba?\u201DHe said, \u201CAt your service!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then the king said, \u201CIs there not still someone of the house
        of Saul, to whom I may show the kindness of God?\u201DAnd Ziba said to the
        king, \u201CThere is still a son of Jonathan who  is  lame in his feet.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "So the king said to him, \u201CWhere is he?\u201DAnd Ziba said to
        the king, \u201CIndeed he is in the house of Machir the son of Ammiel, in
        Lo Debar.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Then King David sent and brought him out of the house of Machir the
        son of Ammiel, from Lo Debar.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Now when Mephibosheth the son of Jonathan, the son of Saul, had come
        to David, he fell on his face and prostrated himself. Then David said, \u201CMephibosheth?\u201DAnd
        he answered, \u201CHere is your servant!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "So David said to him, \u201CDo not fear, for I will surely show you
        kindness for Jonathan your father\u2019s sake, and will restore to you all
        the land of Saul your grandfather; and you shall eat bread at my table continually.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then he bowed himself, and said, \u201CWhat is your servant, that
        you should look upon such a dead dog as I?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And the king called to Ziba, Saul\u2019s servant, and said to him,
        \u201CI have given to your master\u2019s son all that belonged to Saul and
        to all his house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "You therefore, and your sons and your servants, shall work the land
        for him, and you shall bring in the  harvest, that your master\u2019s son
        may have food to eat. But Mephibosheth your master\u2019s son shall eat bread
        at my table always.\u201D Now Ziba had fifteen sons and twenty servants."
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then Ziba said to the king, \u201CAccording to all that my lord the
        king has commanded his servant, so will your servant do.\u201D\u201CAs for
        Mephibosheth,\u201D said  the  king, \u201Che shall eat at my table like
        one of the king\u2019s sons.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Mephibosheth had a young son whose name was Micha. And all who dwelt
        in the house of Ziba were servants of Mephibosheth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "So Mephibosheth dwelt in Jerusalem, for he ate continually at the
        king\u2019s table. And he was lame in both his feet."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Ammonites and Syrians Defeated'
      title: The Ammonites and Syrians Defeated
      number: 1
      content: 'It happened after this that the king of the people of Ammon died,
        and Hanun his son reigned in his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Then David said, \u201CI will show kindness to Hanun the son of Nahash,
        as his father showed kindness to me.\u201DSo David sent by the hand of his
        servants to comfort him concerning his father. And David\u2019s servants
        came into the land of the people of Ammon. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And the princes of the people of Ammon said to Hanun their lord,
        \u201CDo you think that David really honors your father because he has sent
        comforters to you? Has David not rather sent his servants to you to search
        the city, to spy it out, and to overthrow it?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Therefore Hanun took David\u2019s servants, shaved off half of their
        beards, cut off their garments in the middle, at their buttocks, and sent
        them away. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "When they told David, he sent to meet them, because the men were
        greatly ashamed. And the king said, \u201CWait at Jericho until your beards
        have grown, and then return.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'When the people of Ammon saw that they had made themselves repulsive
        to David, the people of Ammon sent and hired the Syrians of Beth Rehob and
        the Syrians of Zoba, twenty thousand foot soldiers; and from the king of
        Maacah one thousand men, and from Ish-Tob twelve thousand men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Now when David heard of  it, he sent Joab and all the army of the
        mighty men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Then the people of Ammon came out and put themselves in battle array
        at the entrance of the gate. And the Syrians of Zoba, Beth Rehob, Ish-Tob,
        and Maacah were by themselves in the field.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "When Joab saw that the battle line was against him before and behind,
        he chose some of Israel\u2019s best and put them in battle array against
        the Syrians. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And the rest of the people he put under the command of Abishai his
        brother, that he might set them in battle array against the people of Ammon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then he said, \u201CIf the Syrians are too strong for me, then you
        shall help me; but if the people of Ammon are too strong for you, then I
        will come and help you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Be of good courage, and let us be strong for our people and for the
        cities of our God. And may the Lord do what  is good in His sight.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So Joab and the people who were with him drew near for the battle
        against the Syrians, and they fled before him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: When the people of Ammon saw that the Syrians were fleeing, they also
        fled before Abishai, and entered the city. So Joab returned from the people
        of Ammon and went to Jerusalem.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'When the Syrians saw that they had been defeated by Israel, they
        gathered together. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then Hadadezer sent and brought out the Syrians who were beyond the
        River, and they came to Helam. And Shobach the commander of Hadadezer\u2019s
        army went before them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'When it was told David, he gathered all Israel, crossed over the
        Jordan, and came to Helam. And the Syrians set themselves in battle array
        against David and fought with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Then the Syrians fled before Israel; and David killed seven hundred
        charioteers and forty thousand horsemen of the Syrians, and struck Shobach
        the commander of their army, who died there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: And when all the kings who  were servants to Hadadezer saw that they
        were defeated by Israel, they made peace with Israel and served them. So
        the Syrians were afraid to help the people of Ammon anymore.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David, Bathsheba, and Uriah'
      title: David, Bathsheba, and Uriah
      number: 1
      content: It happened in the spring of the year, at the time when kings go out
        to  battle, that David sent Joab and his servants with him, and all Israel;
        and they destroyed the people of Ammon and besieged Rabbah. But David remained
        at Jerusalem.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Then it happened one evening that David arose from his bed and walked
        on the roof of the king\u2019s house. And from the roof he saw a woman bathing,
        and the woman was very beautiful to behold. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "So David sent and inquired about the woman. And someone said, \u201CIs
        this not Bathsheba, the daughter of Eliam, the wife of Uriah the Hittite?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then David sent messengers, and took her; and she came to him, and
        he lay with her, for she was cleansed from her impurity; and she returned
        to her house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And the woman conceived; so she sent and told David, and said, \u201CI
        am with child.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then David sent to Joab, saying, \u201CSend me Uriah the Hittite.\u201D
        And Joab sent Uriah to David. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'When Uriah had come to him, David asked how Joab was doing, and how
        the people were doing, and how the war prospered. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And David said to Uriah, \u201CGo down to your house and wash your
        feet.\u201D So Uriah departed from the king\u2019s house, and a gift of 
        food from the king followed him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "But Uriah slept at the door of the king\u2019s house with all the
        servants of his lord, and did not go down to his house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "So when they told David, saying, \u201CUriah did not go down to his
        house,\u201D David said to Uriah, \u201CDid you not come from a journey?
        Why did you not go down to your house?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And Uriah said to David, \u201CThe ark and Israel and Judah are dwelling
        in tents, and my lord Joab and the servants of my lord are encamped in the
        open fields. Shall I then go to my house to eat and drink, and to lie with
        my wife? As you live, and as your soul lives, I will not do this thing.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then David said to Uriah, \u201CWait here today also, and tomorrow
        I will let you depart.\u201D So Uriah remained in Jerusalem that day and
        the next. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Now when David called him, he ate and drank before him; and he made
        him drunk. And at evening he went out to lie on his bed with the servants
        of his lord, but he did not go down to his house.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'In the morning it happened that David wrote a letter to Joab and
        sent it by the hand of Uriah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And he wrote in the letter, saying, \u201CSet Uriah in the forefront
        of the hottest battle, and retreat from him, that he may be struck down and
        die.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So it was, while Joab besieged the city, that he assigned Uriah to
        a place where he knew there were valiant men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Then the men of the city came out and fought with Joab. And some of
        the people of the servants of David fell; and Uriah the Hittite died also.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Then Joab sent and told David all the things concerning the war, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "and charged the messenger, saying, \u201CWhen you have finished telling
        the matters of the war to the king, "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "if it happens that the king\u2019s wrath rises, and he says to you:
        \u2018Why did you approach so near to the city when you fought? Did you not
        know that they would shoot from the wall? "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Who struck Abimelech the son of Jerubbesheth? Was it not a woman
        who cast a piece of a millstone on him from the wall, so that he died in
        Thebez? Why did you go near the wall?\u2019\u2014then you shall say, \u2018Your
        servant Uriah the Hittite is dead also.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'So the messenger went, and came and told David all that Joab had
        sent by him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And the messenger said to David, \u201CSurely the men prevailed against
        us and came out to us in the field; then we drove them back as far as the
        entrance of the gate. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "The archers shot from the wall at your servants; and some of the
        king\u2019s servants are dead, and your servant Uriah the Hittite is dead
        also.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then David said to the messenger, \u201CThus you shall say to Joab:
        \u2018Do not let this thing displease you, for the sword devours one as well
        as another. Strengthen your attack against the city, and overthrow it.\u2019
        So encourage him.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'When the wife of Uriah heard that Uriah her husband was dead, she
        mourned for her husband. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: And when her mourning was over, David sent and brought her to his
        house, and she became his wife and bore him a son. But the thing that David
        had done displeased the Lord.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Nathan\u2019s Parable and David\u2019s Confession"
      title: "Nathan\u2019s Parable and David\u2019s Confession"
      number: 1
      content: "Then the Lord sent Nathan to David. And he came to him, and said
        to him: \u201CThere were two men in one city, one rich and the other poor. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The rich man had exceedingly many flocks and herds. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'But the poor man had nothing, except one little ewe lamb which he
        had bought and nourished; and it grew up together with him and with his children.
        It ate of his own food and drank from his own cup and lay in his bosom; and
        it was like a daughter to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And a traveler came to the rich man, who refused to take from his
        own flock and from his own herd to prepare one for the wayfaring man who
        had come to him; but he took the poor man\u2019s lamb and prepared it for
        the man who had come to him.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "So David\u2019s anger was greatly aroused against the man, and he
        said to Nathan, \u201CAs the Lord lives, the man who has done this shall
        surely die! "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And he shall restore fourfold for the lamb, because he did this thing
        and because he had no pity.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then Nathan said to David, \u201CYou are the man! Thus says the Lord
        God of Israel: \u2018I anointed you king over Israel, and I delivered you
        from the hand of Saul. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "I gave you your master\u2019s house and your master\u2019s wives
        into your keeping, and gave you the house of Israel and Judah. And if that 
        had  been too little, I also would have given you much more! "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Why have you despised the commandment of the Lord, to do evil in
        His sight? You have killed Uriah the Hittite with the sword; you have taken
        his wife to  be your wife, and have killed him with the sword of the people
        of Ammon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Now therefore, the sword shall never depart from your house, because
        you have despised Me, and have taken the wife of Uriah the Hittite to be
        your wife.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Thus says the Lord: \u2018Behold, I will raise up adversity against
        you from your own house; and I will take your wives before your eyes and
        give them to your neighbor, and he shall lie with your wives in the sight
        of this sun. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "For you did it secretly, but I will do this thing before all Israel,
        before the sun.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "So David said to Nathan, \u201CI have sinned against the Lord.\u201DAnd
        Nathan said to David, \u201CThe Lord also has put away your sin; you shall
        not die. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "However, because by this deed you have given great occasion to the
        enemies of the Lord  to blaspheme, the child also who  is born to you shall
        surely die.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "15: The Death of David\u2019s Son"
      title: "The Death of David\u2019s Son"
      number: 15
      content: "Then Nathan departed to his house.And the Lord struck the child that
        Uriah\u2019s wife bore to David, and it became ill. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'David therefore pleaded with God for the child, and David fasted
        and went in and lay all night on the ground. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'So the elders of his house arose and  went to him, to raise him up
        from the ground. But he would not, nor did he eat food with them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then on the seventh day it came to pass that the child died. And
        the servants of David were afraid to tell him that the child was dead. For
        they said, \u201CIndeed, while the child was alive, we spoke to him, and
        he would not heed our voice. How can we tell him that the child is dead?
        He may do some harm!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "When David saw that his servants were whispering, David perceived
        that the child was dead. Therefore David said to his servants, \u201CIs the
        child dead?\u201DAnd they said, \u201CHe is dead.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'So David arose from the ground, washed and anointed himself, and
        changed his clothes; and he went into the house of the Lord and worshiped.
        Then he went to his own house; and when he requested, they set food before
        him, and he ate. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then his servants said to him, \u201CWhat is this that you have done?
        You fasted and wept for the child while  he  was alive, but when the child
        died, you arose and ate food.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And he said, \u201CWhile the child was alive, I fasted and wept;
        for I said, \u2018Who can tell whether the Lord will be gracious to me, that
        the child may live?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: Solomon Is Born'
      title: Solomon Is Born
      number: 23
      content: "But now he is dead; why should I fast? Can I bring him back again?
        I shall go to him, but he shall not return to me.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Then David comforted Bathsheba his wife, and went in to her and lay
        with her. So she bore a son, and he called his name Solomon. Now the Lord
        loved him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: Rabbah Is Captured'
      title: Rabbah Is Captured
      number: 25
      content: 'and He sent word by the hand of Nathan the prophet: So he called
        his name Jedidiah, because of the Lord.'
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Now Joab fought against Rabbah of the people of Ammon, and took the
        royal city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "And Joab sent messengers to David, and said, \u201CI have fought
        against Rabbah, and I have taken the city\u2019s water supply.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Now therefore, gather the rest of the people together and encamp
        against the city and take it, lest I take the city and it be called after
        my name.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'So David gathered all the people together and went to Rabbah, fought
        against it, and took it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Then he took their king\u2019s crown from his head. Its weight was
        a talent of gold, with precious stones. And it was set on David\u2019s head.
        Also he brought out the spoil of the city in great abundance. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: And he brought out the people who were in it, and put them  to  work
        with saws and iron picks and iron axes, and made them cross over to the brick
        works. So he did to all the cities of the people of Ammon. Then David and
        all the people returned to Jerusalem.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Amnon and Tamar'
      title: Amnon and Tamar
      number: 1
      content: 'After this Absalom the son of David had a lovely sister, whose name
        was  Tamar; and Amnon the son of David loved her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Amnon was so distressed over his sister Tamar that he became sick;
        for she was a virgin. And it was improper for Amnon to do anything to her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "But Amnon had a friend whose name was Jonadab the son of Shimeah,
        David\u2019s brother. Now Jonadab was a very crafty man. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And he said to him, \u201CWhy are you, the king\u2019s son, becoming
        thinner day after day? Will you not tell me?\u201DAmnon said to him, \u201CI
        love Tamar, my brother Absalom\u2019s sister.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "So Jonadab said to him, \u201CLie down on your bed and pretend to
        be ill. And when your father comes to see you, say to him, \u2018Please let
        my sister Tamar come and give me food, and prepare the food in my sight,
        that I may see it and eat it from her hand.\u2019 \u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then Amnon lay down and pretended to be ill; and when the king came
        to see him, Amnon said to the king, \u201CPlease let Tamar my sister come
        and make a couple of cakes for me in my sight, that I may eat from her hand.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And David sent home to Tamar, saying, \u201CNow go to your brother
        Amnon\u2019s house, and prepare food for him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "So Tamar went to her brother Amnon\u2019s house; and he was lying
        down. Then she took flour and kneaded it, made cakes in his sight, and baked
        the cakes. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And she took the pan and placed them out before him, but he refused
        to eat. Then Amnon said, \u201CHave everyone go out from me.\u201D And they
        all went out from him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then Amnon said to Tamar, \u201CBring the food into the bedroom,
        that I may eat from your hand.\u201D And Tamar took the cakes which she had
        made, and brought them to Amnon her brother in the bedroom. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Now when she had brought them to him to eat, he took hold of her
        and said to her, \u201CCome, lie with me, my sister.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "But she answered him, \u201CNo, my brother, do not force me, for
        no such thing should be done in Israel. Do not do this disgraceful thing! "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And I, where could I take my shame? And as for you, you would be
        like one of the fools in Israel. Now therefore, please speak to the king;
        for he will not withhold me from you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: However, he would not heed her voice; and being stronger than she,
        he forced her and lay with her.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then Amnon hated her exceedingly, so that the hatred with which he
        hated her was greater than the love with which he had loved her. And Amnon
        said to her, \u201CArise, be gone!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "So she said to him, \u201CNo, indeed! This evil of sending me away
        is worse than the other that you did to me.\u201DBut he would not listen
        to her. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then he called his servant who attended him, and said, \u201CHere!
        Put this woman out, away from me, and bolt the door behind her.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Now she had on a robe of many colors, for the king\u2019s virgin
        daughters wore such apparel. And his servant put her out and bolted the door
        behind her."
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Then Tamar put ashes on her head, and tore her robe of many colors
        that was on her, and laid her hand on her head and went away crying bitterly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And Absalom her brother said to her, \u201CHas Amnon your brother
        been with you? But now hold your peace, my sister. He is your brother; do
        not take this thing to heart.\u201D So Tamar remained desolate in her brother
        Absalom\u2019s house."
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'But when King David heard of all these things, he was very angry. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: Absalom Murders Amnon'
      title: Absalom Murders Amnon
      number: 22
      content: And Absalom spoke to his brother Amnon neither good nor bad. For Absalom
        hated Amnon, because he had forced his sister Tamar.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And it came to pass, after two full years, that Absalom had sheepshearers
        in Baal Hazor, which is near Ephraim; so Absalom invited all the king\u2019s
        sons. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Then Absalom came to the king and said, \u201CKindly note, your servant
        has sheepshearers; please, let the king and his servants go with your servant.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "But the king said to Absalom, \u201CNo, my son, let us not all go
        now, lest we be a burden to you.\u201D Then he urged him, but he would not
        go; and he blessed him."
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Then Absalom said, \u201CIf not, please let my brother Amnon go with
        us.\u201DAnd the king said to him, \u201CWhy should he go with you?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "But Absalom urged him; so he let Amnon and all the king\u2019s sons
        go with him."
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Now Absalom had commanded his servants, saying, \u201CWatch now,
        when Amnon\u2019s heart is merry with wine, and when I say to you, \u2018Strike
        Amnon!\u2019 then kill him. Do not be afraid. Have I not commanded you? Be
        courageous and valiant.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "So the servants of Absalom did to Amnon as Absalom had commanded.
        Then all the king\u2019s sons arose, and each one got on his mule and fled."
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "And it came to pass, while they were on the way, that news came to
        David, saying, \u201CAbsalom has killed all the king\u2019s sons, and not
        one of them is left!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'So the king arose and tore his garments and lay on the ground, and
        all his servants stood by with their clothes torn. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Then Jonadab the son of Shimeah, David\u2019s brother, answered and
        said, \u201CLet not my lord suppose they have killed all the young men, the
        king\u2019s sons, for only Amnon is dead. For by the command of Absalom this
        has been determined from the day that he forced his sister Tamar. "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: Absalom Flees to Geshur'
      title: Absalom Flees to Geshur
      number: 33
      content: "Now therefore, let not my lord the king take the thing to his heart,
        to think that all the king\u2019s sons are dead. For only Amnon is dead.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Then Absalom fled. And the young man who was keeping watch lifted
        his eyes and looked, and there, many people were coming from the road on
        the hillside behind him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "And Jonadab said to the king, \u201CLook, the king\u2019s sons are
        coming; as your servant said, so it is.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "So it was, as soon as he had finished speaking, that the king\u2019s
        sons indeed came, and they lifted up their voice and wept. Also the king
        and all his servants wept very bitterly."
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'But Absalom fled and went to Talmai the son of Ammihud, king of Geshur.
        And David mourned for his son every day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'So Absalom fled and went to Geshur, and was there three years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: And King David longed to go to Absalom. For he had been comforted
        concerning Amnon, because he was dead.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Absalom Returns to Jerusalem'
      title: Absalom Returns to Jerusalem
      number: 1
      content: "So Joab the son of Zeruiah perceived that the king\u2019s heart was
        concerned about Absalom. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And Joab sent to Tekoa and brought from there a wise woman, and said
        to her, \u201CPlease pretend to be a mourner, and put on mourning apparel;
        do not anoint yourself with oil, but act like a woman who has been mourning
        a long time for the dead. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Go to the king and speak to him in this manner.\u201D So Joab put
        the words in her mouth."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And when the woman of Tekoa spoke to the king, she fell on her face
        to the ground and prostrated herself, and said, \u201CHelp, O king!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then the king said to her, \u201CWhat troubles you?\u201DAnd she
        answered, \u201CIndeed I am a widow, my husband is dead. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Now your maidservant had two sons; and the two fought with each other
        in the field, and there  was no one to part them, but the one struck the
        other and killed him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And now the whole family has risen up against your maidservant, and
        they said, \u2018Deliver him who struck his brother, that we may execute
        him for the life of his brother whom he killed; and we will destroy the heir
        also.\u2019 So they would extinguish my ember that is left, and leave to
        my husband neither name nor remnant on the earth.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then the king said to the woman, \u201CGo to your house, and I will
        give orders concerning you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And the woman of Tekoa said to the king, \u201CMy lord, O king, let 
        the iniquity be on me and on my father\u2019s house, and the king and his
        throne be guiltless.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "So the king said, \u201CWhoever says anything to you, bring him to
        me, and he shall not touch you anymore.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then she said, \u201CPlease let the king remember the Lord your God,
        and do not permit the avenger of blood to destroy anymore, lest they destroy
        my son.\u201DAnd he said, \u201CAs the Lord lives, not one hair of your son
        shall fall to the ground.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Therefore the woman said, \u201CPlease, let your maidservant speak
        another word to my lord the king.\u201DAnd he said, \u201CSay on.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "So the woman said: \u201CWhy then have you schemed such a thing against
        the people of God? For the king speaks this thing as one who is guilty, in 
        that the king does not bring his banished one home again. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'For we will surely die and become like water spilled on the ground,
        which cannot be gathered up again. Yet God does not take away a life; but
        He devises means, so that His banished ones are not expelled from Him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Now therefore, I have come to speak of this thing to my lord the
        king because the people have made me afraid. And your maidservant said, \u2018I
        will now speak to the king; it may be that the king will perform the request
        of his maidservant. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "For the king will hear and deliver his maidservant from the hand
        of the man who  would destroy me and my son together from the inheritance
        of God.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Your maidservant said, \u2018The word of my lord the king will now
        be comforting; for as the angel of God, so is my lord the king in discerning
        good and evil. And may the Lord your God be with you.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then the king answered and said to the woman, \u201CPlease do not
        hide from me anything that I ask you.\u201DAnd the woman said, \u201CPlease,
        let my lord the king speak.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "So the king said, \u201CIs the hand of Joab with you in all this?\u201D
        And the woman answered and said, \u201CAs you live, my lord the king, no
        one can turn to the right hand or to the left from anything that my lord
        the king has spoken. For your servant Joab commanded me, and he put all these
        words in the mouth of your maidservant. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "To bring about this change of affairs your servant Joab has done
        this thing; but my lord is wise, according to the wisdom of the angel of
        God, to know everything that is in the earth.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And the king said to Joab, \u201CAll right, I have granted this thing.
        Go therefore, bring back the young man Absalom.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then Joab fell to the ground on his face and bowed himself, and thanked
        the king. And Joab said, \u201CToday your servant knows that I have found
        favor in your sight, my lord, O king, in that the king has fulfilled the
        request of his servant.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'So Joab arose and went to Geshur, and brought Absalom to Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: David Forgives Absalom'
      title: David Forgives Absalom
      number: 24
      content: "And the king said, \u201CLet him return to his own house, but do
        not let him see my face.\u201D So Absalom returned to his own house, but
        did not see the king\u2019s face."
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Now in all Israel there was no one who was praised as much as Absalom
        for his good looks. From the sole of his foot to the crown of his head there
        was no blemish in him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "And when he cut the hair of his head\u2014at the end of every year
        he cut it because it was heavy on him\u2014when he cut it, he weighed the
        hair of his head at two hundred shekels according to the king\u2019s standard. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: To Absalom were born three sons, and one daughter whose name was Tamar.
        She was a woman of beautiful appearance.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "And Absalom dwelt two full years in Jerusalem, but did not see the
        king\u2019s face. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Therefore Absalom sent for Joab, to send him to the king, but he
        would not come to him. And when he sent again the second time, he would not
        come. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "So he said to his servants, \u201CSee, Joab\u2019s field is near
        mine, and he has barley there; go and set it on fire.\u201D And Absalom\u2019s
        servants set the field on fire."
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Then Joab arose and came to Absalom\u2019s house, and said to him,
        \u201CWhy have your servants set my field on fire?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "And Absalom answered Joab, \u201CLook, I sent to you, saying, \u2018Come
        here, so that I may send you to the king, to say, \u201CWhy have I come from
        Geshur? It  would  be better for me to  be there still.\u201D \u2019 Now
        therefore, let me see the king\u2019s face; but if there is iniquity in me,
        let him execute me.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: So Joab went to the king and told him. And when he had called for
        Absalom, he came to the king and bowed himself on his face to the ground
        before the king. Then the king kissed Absalom.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Absalom\u2019s Treason"
      title: "Absalom\u2019s Treason"
      number: 1
      content: 'After this it happened that Absalom provided himself with chariots
        and horses, and fifty men to run before him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Now Absalom would rise early and stand beside the way to the gate.
        So it was, whenever anyone who had a lawsuit came to the king for a decision,
        that Absalom would call to him and say, \u201CWhat city are you from?\u201D
        And he would say, \u201CYour servant is from such and such a tribe of Israel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then Absalom would say to him, \u201CLook, your case is good and
        right; but there  is no deputy of the king to hear you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Moreover Absalom would say, \u201COh, that I were made judge in the
        land, and everyone who has any suit or cause would come to me; then I would
        give him justice.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And so it was, whenever anyone came near to bow down to him, that
        he would put out his hand and take him and kiss him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: In this manner Absalom acted toward all Israel who came to the king
        for judgment. So Absalom stole the hearts of the men of Israel.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Now it came to pass after forty years that Absalom said to the king,
        \u201CPlease, let me go to Hebron and pay the vow which I made to the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "For your servant took a vow while I dwelt at Geshur in Syria, saying,
        \u2018If the Lord indeed brings me back to Jerusalem, then I will serve the
        Lord.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And the king said to him, \u201CGo in peace.\u201D So he arose and
        went to Hebron."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then Absalom sent spies throughout all the tribes of Israel, saying,
        \u201CAs soon as you hear the sound of the trumpet, then you shall say, \u2018Absalom
        reigns in Hebron!\u2019 \u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And with Absalom went two hundred men invited from Jerusalem, and
        they went along innocently and did not know anything. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: David Escapes from Jerusalem'
      title: David Escapes from Jerusalem
      number: 12
      content: "Then Absalom sent for Ahithophel the Gilonite, David\u2019s counselor,
        from his city\u2014from Giloh\u2014while he offered sacrifices. And the conspiracy
        grew strong, for the people with Absalom continually increased in number."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Now a messenger came to David, saying, \u201CThe hearts of the men
        of Israel are with Absalom.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "So David said to all his servants who were with him at Jerusalem,
        \u201CArise, and let us flee, or we shall not escape from Absalom. Make haste
        to depart, lest he overtake us suddenly and bring disaster upon us, and strike
        the city with the edge of the sword.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And the king\u2019s servants said to the king, \u201CWe are your
        servants, ready  to  do whatever my lord the king commands.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then the king went out with all his household after him. But the
        king left ten women, concubines, to keep the house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And the king went out with all the people after him, and stopped
        at the outskirts. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Then all his servants passed before him; and all the Cherethites,
        all the Pelethites, and all the Gittites, six hundred men who had followed
        him from Gath, passed before the king.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then the king said to Ittai the Gittite, \u201CWhy are you also going
        with us? Return and remain with the king. For you are a foreigner and also
        an exile from your own place. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "In fact, you came only yesterday. Should I make you wander up and
        down with us today, since I go I know not where? Return, and take your brethren
        back. Mercy and truth be with you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "But Ittai answered the king and said, \u201CAs the Lord lives, and
        as my lord the king lives, surely in whatever place my lord the king shall
        be, whether in death or life, even there also your servant will be.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "So David said to Ittai, \u201CGo, and cross over.\u201D Then Ittai
        the Gittite and all his men and all the little ones who were with him crossed
        over. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: And all the country wept with a loud voice, and all the people crossed
        over. The king himself also crossed over the Brook Kidron, and all the people
        crossed over toward the way of the wilderness.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'There was Zadok also, and all the Levites with him, bearing the ark
        of the covenant of God. And they set down the ark of God, and Abiathar went
        up until all the people had finished crossing over from the city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then the king said to Zadok, \u201CCarry the ark of God back into
        the city. If I find favor in the eyes of the Lord, He will bring me back
        and show me both it and His dwelling place. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "But if He says thus: \u2018I have no delight in you,\u2019 here I
        am, let Him do to me as seems good to Him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "The king also said to Zadok the priest, \u201CAre you not a seer?
        Return to the city in peace, and your two sons with you, Ahimaaz your son,
        and Jonathan the son of Abiathar. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "See, I will wait in the plains of the wilderness until word comes
        from you to inform me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: Therefore Zadok and Abiathar carried the ark of God back to Jerusalem.
        And they remained there.
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'So David went up by the Ascent of the Mount  of Olives, and wept
        as he went up; and he had his head covered and went barefoot. And all the
        people who were with him covered their heads and went up, weeping as they
        went up. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Then someone told David, saying, \u201CAhithophel is among the conspirators
        with Absalom.\u201D And David said, \u201CO Lord, I pray, turn the counsel
        of Ahithophel into foolishness!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Now it happened when David had come to the top of  the  mountain,
        where he worshiped God\u2014there was Hushai the Archite coming to meet him
        with his robe torn and dust on his head. "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "David said to him, \u201CIf you go on with me, then you will become
        a burden to me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "But if you return to the city, and say to Absalom, \u2018I will be
        your servant, O king; as I was your father\u2019s servant previously, so
        I will now also be your servant,\u2019 then you may defeat the counsel of
        Ahithophel for me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "And do you not have Zadok and Abiathar the priests with you there?
        Therefore it will be that whatever you hear from the king\u2019s house, you
        shall tell to Zadok and Abiathar the priests. "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Indeed they  have there with them their two sons, Ahimaaz, Zadok\u2019s
        son, and Jonathan, Abiathar\u2019s son; and by them you shall send me everything
        you hear.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "So Hushai, David\u2019s friend, went into the city. And Absalom came
        into Jerusalem."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Mephibosheth\u2019s Servant"
      title: "Mephibosheth\u2019s Servant"
      number: 1
      content: 'When David was a little past the top of  the  mountain, there was
        Ziba the servant of Mephibosheth, who met him with a couple of saddled donkeys,
        and on them two hundred loaves of bread, one hundred clusters of raisins,
        one hundred summer fruits, and a skin of wine. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And the king said to Ziba, \u201CWhat do you mean to do with these?\u201DSo
        Ziba said, \u201CThe donkeys are for the king\u2019s household to ride on,
        the bread and summer fruit for the young men to eat, and the wine for those
        who are faint in the wilderness to drink.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then the king said, \u201CAnd where is your master\u2019s son?\u201DAnd
        Ziba said to the king, \u201CIndeed he is staying in Jerusalem, for he said,
        \u2018Today the house of Israel will restore the kingdom of my father to
        me.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: Shimei Curses David'
      title: Shimei Curses David
      number: 4
      content: "So the king said to Ziba, \u201CHere, all that belongs to Mephibosheth
        is yours.\u201DAnd Ziba said, \u201CI humbly bow before you, that I may find
        favor in your sight, my lord, O king!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Now when King David came to Bahurim, there was a man from the family
        of the house of Saul, whose name was  Shimei the son of Gera, coming from
        there. He came out, cursing continuously as he came. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And he threw stones at David and at all the servants of King David.
        And all the people and all the mighty men were on his right hand and on his
        left. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Also Shimei said thus when he cursed: \u201CCome out! Come out! You
        bloodthirsty man, you rogue! "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "The Lord has brought upon you all the blood of the house of Saul,
        in whose place you have reigned; and the Lord has delivered the kingdom into
        the hand of Absalom your son. So now you are  caught in your own evil, because
        you are a bloodthirsty man!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then Abishai the son of Zeruiah said to the king, \u201CWhy should
        this dead dog curse my lord the king? Please, let me go over and take off
        his head!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "But the king said, \u201CWhat have I to do with you, you sons of
        Zeruiah? So let him curse, because the Lord has said to him, \u2018Curse
        David.\u2019 Who then shall say, \u2018Why have you done so?\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And David said to Abishai and all his servants, \u201CSee how my
        son who came from my own body seeks my life. How much more now may  this
        Benjamite? Let him alone, and let him curse; for so the Lord has ordered
        him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "It may be that the Lord will look on my affliction, and that the
        Lord will repay me with good for his cursing this day.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And as David and his men went along the road, Shimei went along the
        hillside opposite him and cursed as he went, threw stones at him and kicked
        up dust. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: The Advice of Ahithophel'
      title: The Advice of Ahithophel
      number: 14
      content: Now the king and all the people who were with him became weary; so
        they refreshed themselves there.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Meanwhile Absalom and all the people, the men of Israel, came to
        Jerusalem; and Ahithophel was with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And so it was, when Hushai the Archite, David\u2019s friend, came
        to Absalom, that Hushai said to Absalom, \u201CLong live the king! Long live
        the king!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "So Absalom said to Hushai, \u201CIs this your loyalty to your friend?
        Why did you not go with your friend?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And Hushai said to Absalom, \u201CNo, but whom the Lord and this
        people and all the men of Israel choose, his I will be, and with him I will
        remain. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Furthermore, whom should I serve? Should  I not serve in the presence
        of his son? As I have served in your father\u2019s presence, so will I be
        in your presence.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then Absalom said to Ahithophel, \u201CGive advice as to what we
        should do.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And Ahithophel said to Absalom, \u201CGo in to your father\u2019s
        concubines, whom he has left to keep the house; and all Israel will hear
        that you are abhorred by your father. Then the hands of all who are with
        you will be strong.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "So they pitched a tent for Absalom on the top of the house, and Absalom
        went in to his father\u2019s concubines in the sight of all Israel."
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: Now the advice of Ahithophel, which he gave in those days, was as
        if one had inquired at the oracle of God. So was all the advice of Ahithophel
        both with David and with Absalom.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "Moreover Ahithophel said to Absalom, \u201CNow let me choose twelve
        thousand men, and I will arise and pursue David tonight. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'I will come upon him while he is  weary and weak, and make him afraid.
        And all the people who are with him will flee, and I will strike only the
        king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then I will bring back all the people to you. When all return except
        the man whom you seek, all the people will be at peace.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: The Advice of Hushai'
      title: The Advice of Hushai
      number: 4
      content: And the saying pleased Absalom and all the elders of Israel.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then Absalom said, \u201CNow call Hushai the Archite also, and let
        us hear what he says too.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And when Hushai came to Absalom, Absalom spoke to him, saying, \u201CAhithophel
        has spoken in this manner. Shall we do as he says? If not, speak up.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "So Hushai said to Absalom: \u201CThe advice that Ahithophel has given
        is not good at this time. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "For,\u201D said Hushai, \u201Cyou know your father and his men, that
        they are mighty men, and they are enraged in their minds, like a bear robbed
        of her cubs in the field; and your father is a man of war, and will not camp
        with the people. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Surely by now he is hidden in some pit, or in some other place. And
        it will be, when some of them are overthrown at the first, that whoever hears
        it will say, \u2018There is a slaughter among the people who follow Absalom.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And even he who  is valiant, whose heart is like the heart of a lion,
        will melt completely. For all Israel knows that your father is a mighty man,
        and those who are with him are valiant men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Therefore I advise that all Israel be fully gathered to you, from
        Dan to Beersheba, like the sand that is by the sea for multitude, and that
        you go to battle in person. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'So we will come upon him in some place where he may be found, and
        we will fall on him as the dew falls on the ground. And of him and all the
        men who are with him there shall not be left so much as one. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Moreover, if he has withdrawn into a city, then all Israel shall
        bring ropes to that city; and we will pull it into the river, until there
        is not one small stone found there.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: Hushai Warns David to Escape'
      title: Hushai Warns David to Escape
      number: 14
      content: "So Absalom and all the men of Israel said, \u201CThe advice of Hushai
        the Archite is better than the advice of Ahithophel.\u201D For the Lord had
        purposed to defeat the good advice of Ahithophel, to the intent that the
        Lord might bring disaster on Absalom."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then Hushai said to Zadok and Abiathar the priests, \u201CThus and
        so Ahithophel advised Absalom and the elders of Israel, and thus and so I
        have advised. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Now therefore, send quickly and tell David, saying, \u2018Do not
        spend this night in the plains of the wilderness, but speedily cross over,
        lest the king and all the people who are with him be swallowed up.\u2019
        \u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Now Jonathan and Ahimaaz stayed at En Rogel, for they dared not be
        seen coming into the city; so a female servant would come and tell them,
        and they would go and tell King David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Nevertheless a lad saw them, and told Absalom. But both of them went
        away quickly and came to a man\u2019s house in Bahurim, who had a well in
        his court; and they went down into it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then the woman took and spread a covering over the well\u2019s mouth,
        and spread ground grain on it; and the thing was not known. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And when Absalom\u2019s servants came to the woman at the house,
        they said, \u201CWhere are Ahimaaz and Jonathan?\u201DSo the woman said to
        them, \u201CThey have gone over the water brook.\u201DAnd when they had searched
        and could not find them, they returned to Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Now it came to pass, after they had departed, that they came up out
        of the well and went and told King David, and said to David, \u201CArise
        and cross over the water quickly. For thus has Ahithophel advised against
        you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: So David and all the people who were with him arose and crossed over
        the Jordan. By morning light not one of them was left who had not gone over
        the Jordan.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Now when Ahithophel saw that his advice was not followed, he saddled
        a donkey, and arose and went home to his house, to his city. Then he put
        his household in order, and hanged himself, and died; and he was buried in
        his father\u2019s tomb."
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Then David went to Mahanaim. And Absalom crossed over the Jordan,
        he and all the men of Israel with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "And Absalom made Amasa captain of the army instead of Joab. This
        Amasa was the son of a man whose name was Jithra, an Israelite, who had gone
        in to Abigail the daughter of Nahash, sister of Zeruiah, Joab\u2019s mother. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: So Israel and Absalom encamped in the land of Gilead.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Now it happened, when David had come to Mahanaim, that Shobi the
        son of Nahash from Rabbah of the people of Ammon, Machir the son of Ammiel
        from Lo Debar, and Barzillai the Gileadite from Rogelim, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'brought beds and basins, earthen vessels and wheat, barley and flour,
        parched grain and beans, lentils and parched seeds,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "honey and curds, sheep and cheese of the herd, for David and the
        people who were with him to eat. For they said, \u201CThe people are hungry
        and weary and thirsty in the wilderness.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Absalom\u2019s Defeat and Death"
      title: "Absalom\u2019s Defeat and Death"
      number: 1
      content: 'And David numbered the people who were with him, and set captains
        of thousands and captains of hundreds over them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Then David sent out one third of the people under the hand of Joab,
        one third under the hand of Abishai the son of Zeruiah, Joab\u2019s brother,
        and one third under the hand of Ittai the Gittite. And the king said to the
        people, \u201CI also will surely go out with you myself.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "But the people answered, \u201CYou shall not go out! For if we flee
        away, they will not care about us; nor if half of us die, will they care
        about us. But you  are worth ten thousand of us now. For you are now more
        help to us in the city.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then the king said to them, \u201CWhatever seems best to you I will
        do.\u201D So the king stood beside the gate, and all the people went out
        by hundreds and by thousands. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Now the king had commanded Joab, Abishai, and Ittai, saying, \u201CDeal
        gently for my sake with the young man Absalom.\u201D And all the people heard
        when the king gave all the captains orders concerning Absalom."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So the people went out into the field of battle against Israel. And
        the battle was in the woods of Ephraim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The people of Israel were overthrown there before the servants of
        David, and a great slaughter of twenty thousand took place there that day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: For the battle there was scattered over the face of the whole countryside,
        and the woods devoured more people that day than the sword devoured.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then Absalom met the servants of David. Absalom rode on a mule. The
        mule went under the thick boughs of a great terebinth tree, and his head
        caught in the terebinth; so he was left hanging between heaven and earth.
        And the mule which was under him went on. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Now a certain man saw it and told Joab, and said, \u201CI just saw
        Absalom hanging in a terebinth tree!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "So Joab said to the man who told him, \u201CYou just saw him! And
        why did you not strike him there to the ground? I would have given you ten
        shekels of silver and a belt.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "But the man said to Joab, \u201CThough I were to receive a thousand
        shekels of silver in my hand, I would not raise my hand against the king\u2019s
        son. For in our hearing the king commanded you and Abishai and Ittai, saying,
        \u2018Beware lest anyone touch the young man Absalom!\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Otherwise I would have dealt falsely against my own life. For there
        is nothing hidden from the king, and you yourself would have set yourself
        against me.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then Joab said, \u201CI cannot linger with you.\u201D And he took
        three spears in his hand and thrust them through Absalom\u2019s heart, while
        he was still alive in the midst of the terebinth tree. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And ten young men who bore Joab\u2019s armor surrounded Absalom,
        and struck and killed him."
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So Joab blew the trumpet, and the people returned from pursuing Israel.
        For Joab held back the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: And they took Absalom and cast him into a large pit in the woods,
        and laid a very large heap of stones over him. Then all Israel fled, everyone
        to his tent.
      comments: []
    - name: "18: David Hears of Absalom\u2019s Death"
      title: "David Hears of Absalom\u2019s Death"
      number: 18
      content: "Now Absalom in his lifetime had taken and set up a pillar for himself,
        which is in the King\u2019s Valley. For he said, \u201CI have no son to keep
        my name in remembrance.\u201D He called the pillar after his own name. And
        to this day it is called Absalom\u2019s Monument."
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then Ahimaaz the son of Zadok said, \u201CLet me run now and take
        the news to the king, how the Lord has avenged him of his enemies.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And Joab said to him, \u201CYou shall not take the news this day,
        for you shall take the news another day. But today you shall take no news,
        because the king\u2019s son is dead.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then Joab said to the Cushite, \u201CGo, tell the king what you have
        seen.\u201D So the Cushite bowed himself to Joab and ran."
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And Ahimaaz the son of Zadok said again to Joab, \u201CBut whatever
        happens, please let me also run after the Cushite.\u201DSo Joab said, \u201CWhy
        will you run, my son, since you have no news ready?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CBut whatever happens,\u201D he  said, \u201Clet me run.\u201DSo
        he said to him, \u201CRun.\u201D Then Ahimaaz ran by way of the plain, and
        outran the Cushite."
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Now David was sitting between the two gates. And the watchman went
        up to the roof over the gate, to the wall, lifted his eyes and looked, and
        there was a man, running alone. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then the watchman cried out and told the king. And the king said,
        \u201CIf he is alone, there  is news in his mouth.\u201D And he came rapidly
        and drew near."
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Then the watchman saw another man running, and the watchman called
        to the gatekeeper and said, \u201CThere is another man, running alone!\u201DAnd
        the king said, \u201CHe also brings news.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "So the watchman said, \u201CI think the running of the first is like
        the running of Ahimaaz the son of Zadok.\u201DAnd the king said, \u201CHe
        is a good man, and comes with good news.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "So Ahimaaz called out and said to the king, \u201CAll is well!\u201D
        Then he bowed down with his face to the earth before the king, and said,
        \u201CBlessed be the Lord your God, who has delivered up the men who raised
        their hand against my lord the king!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "The king said, \u201CIs the young man Absalom safe?\u201DAhimaaz
        answered, \u201CWhen Joab sent the king\u2019s servant and me your servant,
        I saw a great tumult, but I did not know what it  was  about.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "And the king said, \u201CTurn aside and stand here.\u201D So he turned
        aside and stood still."
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Just then the Cushite came, and the Cushite said, \u201CThere is
        good news, my lord the king! For the Lord has avenged you this day of all
        those who rose against you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: "32: David\u2019s Mourning for Absalom"
      title: "David\u2019s Mourning for Absalom"
      number: 32
      content: "And the king said to the Cushite, \u201CIs the young man Absalom
        safe?\u201DSo the Cushite answered, \u201CMay the enemies of my lord the
        king, and all who rise against you to do harm, be like that young man!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Then the king was deeply moved, and went up to the chamber over the
        gate, and wept. And as he went, he said thus: \u201CO my son Absalom\u2014my
        son, my son Absalom\u2014if only I had died in your place! O Absalom my son,
        my son!\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "And Joab was told, \u201CBehold, the king is weeping and mourning
        for Absalom.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "So the victory that day was turned into mourning for all the people.
        For the people heard it said that day, \u201CThe king is grieved for his
        son.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And the people stole back into the city that day, as people who are
        ashamed steal away when they flee in battle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "But the king covered his face, and the king cried out with a loud
        voice, \u201CO my son Absalom! O Absalom, my son, my son!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then Joab came into the house to the king, and said, \u201CToday
        you have disgraced all your servants who today have saved your life, the
        lives of your sons and daughters, the lives of your wives and the lives of
        your concubines, "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'in that you love your enemies and hate your friends. For you have
        declared today that you regard neither princes nor servants; for today I
        perceive that if Absalom had lived and all of us had died today, then it
        would have pleased you well. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Now therefore, arise, go out and speak comfort to your servants.
        For I swear by the Lord, if you do not go out, not one will stay with you
        this night. And that will be worse for you than all the evil that has befallen
        you from your youth until now.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: David Returns to Jerusalem'
      title: David Returns to Jerusalem
      number: 8
      content: "Then the king arose and sat in the gate. And they told all the people,
        saying, \u201CThere is the king, sitting in the gate.\u201D So all the people
        came before the king.For everyone of Israel had fled to his tent."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Now all the people were in a dispute throughout all the tribes of
        Israel, saying, \u201CThe king saved us from the hand of our enemies, he
        delivered us from the hand of the Philistines, and now he has fled from the
        land because of Absalom. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "But Absalom, whom we anointed over us, has died in battle. Now therefore,
        why do you say nothing about bringing back the king?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "So King David sent to Zadok and Abiathar the priests, saying, \u201CSpeak
        to the elders of Judah, saying, \u2018Why are you the last to bring the king
        back to his house, since the words of all Israel have come to the king, to
        his very house? "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "You are my brethren, you are  my bone and my flesh. Why then are
        you the last to bring back the king?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And say to Amasa, \u2018Are you not my bone and my flesh? God do
        so to me, and more also, if you are not commander of the army before me continually
        in place of Joab.\u2019 \u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "So he swayed the hearts of all the men of Judah, just as the  heart 
        of one man, so that they sent this  word to the king: \u201CReturn, you and
        all your servants!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then the king returned and came to the Jordan. And Judah came to
        Gilgal, to go to meet the king, to escort the king across the Jordan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And Shimei the son of Gera, a Benjamite, who was from Bahurim, hurried
        and came down with the men of Judah to meet King David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'There  were a thousand men of Benjamin with him, and Ziba the servant
        of the house of Saul, and his fifteen sons and his twenty servants with him;
        and they went over the Jordan before the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: "18: David\u2019s Mercy to Shimei"
      title: "David\u2019s Mercy to Shimei"
      number: 18
      content: "Then a ferryboat went across to carry over the king\u2019s household,
        and to do what he thought good.Now Shimei the son of Gera fell down before
        the king when he had crossed the Jordan. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then he said to the king, \u201CDo not let my lord impute iniquity
        to me, or remember what wrong your servant did on the day that my lord the
        king left Jerusalem, that the king should take it to heart. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "For I, your servant, know that I have sinned. Therefore here I am,
        the first to come today of all the house of Joseph to go down to meet my
        lord the king.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "But Abishai the son of Zeruiah answered and said, \u201CShall not
        Shimei be put to death for this, because he cursed the Lord\u2019s anointed?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And David said, \u201CWhat have I to do with you, you sons of Zeruiah,
        that you should be adversaries to me today? Shall any man be put to death
        today in Israel? For do I not know that today I am king over Israel?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: David and Mephibosheth Meet'
      title: David and Mephibosheth Meet
      number: 23
      content: "Therefore the king said to Shimei, \u201CYou shall not die.\u201D
        And the king swore to him."
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Now Mephibosheth the son of Saul came down to meet the king. And
        he had not cared for his feet, nor trimmed his mustache, nor washed his clothes,
        from the day the king departed until the day he returned in peace. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "So it was, when he had come to Jerusalem to meet the king, that the
        king said to him, \u201CWhy did you not go with me, Mephibosheth?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "And he answered, \u201CMy lord, O king, my servant deceived me. For
        your servant said, \u2018I will saddle a donkey for myself, that I may ride
        on it and go to the king,\u2019 because your servant is lame. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And he has slandered your servant to my lord the king, but my lord
        the king is like the angel of God. Therefore do what  is good in your eyes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "For all my father\u2019s house were but dead men before my lord the
        king. Yet you set your servant among those who eat at your own table. Therefore
        what right have I still to cry out anymore to the king?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "So the king said to him, \u201CWhy do you speak anymore of your matters?
        I have said, \u2018You and Ziba divide the land.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: "30: David\u2019s Kindness to Barzillai"
      title: "David\u2019s Kindness to Barzillai"
      number: 30
      content: "Then Mephibosheth said to the king, \u201CRather, let him take it
        all, inasmuch as my lord the king has come back in peace to his own house.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'And Barzillai the Gileadite came down from Rogelim and went across
        the Jordan with the king, to escort him across the Jordan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Now Barzillai was a very aged man, eighty years old. And he had provided
        the king with supplies while he stayed at Mahanaim, for he was a very rich
        man. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "And the king said to Barzillai, \u201CCome across with me, and I
        will provide for you while you are with me in Jerusalem.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "But Barzillai said to the king, \u201CHow long have I to live, that
        I should go up with the king to Jerusalem? "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'I am today eighty years old. Can I discern between the good and bad?
        Can your servant taste what I eat or what I drink? Can I hear any longer
        the voice of singing men and singing women? Why then should your servant
        be a further burden to my lord the king? '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Your servant will go a little way across the Jordan with the king.
        And why should the king repay me with such a reward? '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Please let your servant turn back again, that I may die in my own
        city, near the grave of my father and mother. But here is your servant Chimham;
        let him cross over with my lord the king, and do for him what seems good
        to you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "And the king answered, \u201CChimham shall cross over with me, and
        I will do for him what seems good to you. Now whatever you request of me,
        I will do for you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: The Quarrel About the King'
      title: The Quarrel About the King
      number: 39
      content: Then all the people went over the Jordan. And when the king had crossed
        over, the king kissed Barzillai and blessed him, and he returned to his own
        place.
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'Now the king went on to Gilgal, and Chimham went on with him. And
        all the people of Judah escorted the king, and also half the people of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "Just then all the men of Israel came to the king, and said to the
        king, \u201CWhy have our brethren, the men of Judah, stolen you away and
        brought the king, his household, and all David\u2019s men with him across
        the Jordan?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "So all the men of Judah answered the men of Israel, \u201CBecause
        the king is  a close relative of ours. Why then are you angry over this matter?
        Have we ever eaten at the king\u2019s expense? Or has he given us any gift?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "And the men of Israel answered the men of Judah, and said, \u201CWe
        have ten shares in the king; therefore we also have more right to David than
        you. Why then do you despise us\u2014were we not the first to advise bringing
        back our king?\u201DYet the words of the men of Judah were fiercer than the
        words of the men of Israel."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Rebellion of Sheba'
      title: The Rebellion of Sheba
      number: 1
      content: "And there happened to be there a rebel, whose name was Sheba the
        son of Bichri, a Benjamite. And he blew a trumpet, and said:\u201CWe have
        no share in David,Nor do we have inheritance in the son of Jesse;Every man
        to his tents, O Israel!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: So every man of Israel deserted David, and followed Sheba the son
        of Bichri. But the men of Judah, from the Jordan as far as Jerusalem, remained
        loyal to their king.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Now David came to his house at Jerusalem. And the king took the ten
        women, his concubines whom he had left to keep the house, and put them in
        seclusion and supported them, but did not go in to them. So they were shut
        up to the day of their death, living in widowhood.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And the king said to Amasa, \u201CAssemble the men of Judah for me
        within three days, and be present here yourself.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So Amasa went to assemble the  men  of Judah. But he delayed longer
        than the set time which David had appointed him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And David said to Abishai, \u201CNow Sheba the son of Bichri will
        do us more harm than Absalom. Take your lord\u2019s servants and pursue him,
        lest he find for himself fortified cities, and escape us.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "So Joab\u2019s men, with the Cherethites, the Pelethites, and all
        the mighty men, went out after him. And they went out of Jerusalem to pursue
        Sheba the son of Bichri. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'When they were at the large stone which is in Gibeon, Amasa came
        before them. Now Joab was dressed in battle armor; on it was a belt with
        a sword fastened in its sheath at his hips; and as he was going forward,
        it fell out. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then Joab said to Amasa, \u201CAre you in health, my brother?\u201D
        And Joab took Amasa by the beard with his right hand to kiss him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "But Amasa did not notice the sword that was in Joab\u2019s hand.
        And he struck him with it in the stomach, and his entrails poured out on
        the ground; and he did not strike him again. Thus he died.Then Joab and Abishai
        his brother pursued Sheba the son of Bichri. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Meanwhile one of Joab\u2019s men stood near Amasa, and said, \u201CWhoever
        favors Joab and whoever is for David\u2014follow Joab!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'But Amasa wallowed in his blood in the middle of the highway. And
        when the man saw that all the people stood still, he moved Amasa from the
        highway to the field and threw a garment over him, when he saw that everyone
        who came upon him halted. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: When he was removed from the highway, all the people went on after
        Joab to pursue Sheba the son of Bichri.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And he went through all the tribes of Israel to Abel and Beth Maachah
        and all the Berites. So they were gathered together and also went after Sheba.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Then they came and besieged him in Abel of Beth Maachah; and they
        cast up a siege mound against the city, and it stood by the rampart. And
        all the people who were with Joab battered the wall to throw it down.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then a wise woman cried out from the city, \u201CHear, hear! Please
        say to Joab, \u2018Come nearby, that I may speak with you.\u2019 \u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "When he had come near to her, the woman said, \u201CAre you Joab?\u201DHe
        answered, \u201CI am.\u201DThen she said to him, \u201CHear the words of
        your maidservant.\u201DAnd he answered, \u201CI am listening.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "So she spoke, saying, \u201CThey used to talk in former times, saying,
        \u2018They shall surely seek guidance at Abel,\u2019 and so they would end
        disputes.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "I am  among  the peaceable and faithful in Israel. You seek to destroy
        a city and a mother in Israel. Why would you swallow up the inheritance of
        the Lord?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And Joab answered and said, \u201CFar be it, far be it from me, that
        I should swallow up or destroy! "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "That is not so. But a man from the mountains of Ephraim, Sheba the
        son of Bichri by name, has raised his hand against the king, against David.
        Deliver him only, and I will depart from the city.\u201DSo the woman said
        to Joab, \u201CWatch, his head will be thrown to you over the wall.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "22: David\u2019s Government Officers"
      title: "David\u2019s Government Officers"
      number: 22
      content: Then the woman in her wisdom went to all the people. And they cut
        off the head of Sheba the son of Bichri, and threw it out to Joab. Then he
        blew a trumpet, and they withdrew from the city, every man to his tent. So
        Joab returned to the king at Jerusalem.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And Joab was over all the army of Israel; Benaiah the son of Jehoiada
        was over the Cherethites and the Pelethites; '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Adoram was  in charge of revenue; Jehoshaphat the son of Ahilud was
        recorder; '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Sheva was scribe; Zadok and Abiathar were the priests; '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: and Ira the Jairite was a chief minister under David.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David Avenges the Gibeonites'
      title: David Avenges the Gibeonites
      number: 1
      content: "Now there was a famine in the days of David for three years, year
        after year; and David inquired of the Lord. And the Lord answered, \u201CIt 
        is because of Saul and his bloodthirsty house, because he killed the Gibeonites.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: So the king called the Gibeonites and spoke to them. Now the Gibeonites
        were not of the children of Israel, but of the remnant of the Amorites; the
        children of Israel had sworn protection to them, but Saul had sought to kill
        them in his zeal for the children of Israel and Judah.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Therefore David said to the Gibeonites, \u201CWhat shall I do for
        you? And with what shall I make atonement, that you may bless the inheritance
        of the Lord?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And the Gibeonites said to him, \u201CWe will have no silver or gold
        from Saul or from his house, nor shall you kill any man in Israel for us.\u201DSo
        he said, \u201CWhatever you say, I will do for you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then they answered the king, \u201CAs for the man who consumed us
        and plotted against us, that we should be destroyed from remaining in any
        of the territories of Israel, "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "let seven men of his descendants be delivered to us, and we will
        hang them before the Lord  in Gibeah of Saul, whom the Lord chose.\u201DAnd
        the king said, \u201CI will give them.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "But the king spared Mephibosheth the son of Jonathan, the son of
        Saul, because of the Lord\u2019s oath that was between them, between David
        and Jonathan the son of Saul. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So the king took Armoni and Mephibosheth, the two sons of Rizpah
        the daughter of Aiah, whom she bore to Saul, and the five sons of Michal
        the daughter of Saul, whom she brought up for Adriel the son of Barzillai
        the Meholathite; '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: and he delivered them into the hands of the Gibeonites, and they hanged
        them on the hill before the Lord. So they fell, all seven together, and were
        put to death in the days of harvest, in the first days, in the beginning
        of barley harvest.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Now Rizpah the daughter of Aiah took sackcloth and spread it for herself
        on the rock, from the beginning of harvest until the late rains poured on
        them from heaven. And she did not allow the birds of the air to rest on them
        by day nor the beasts of the field by night.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And David was told what Rizpah the daughter of Aiah, the concubine
        of Saul, had done. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then David went and took the bones of Saul, and the bones of Jonathan
        his son, from the men of Jabesh Gilead who had stolen them from the street
        of Beth Shan, where the Philistines had hung them up, after the Philistines
        had struck down Saul in Gilboa. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So he brought up the bones of Saul and the bones of Jonathan his
        son from there; and they gathered the bones of those who had been hanged. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: Philistine Giants Destroyed'
      title: Philistine Giants Destroyed
      number: 14
      content: They buried the bones of Saul and Jonathan his son in the country
        of Benjamin in Zelah, in the tomb of Kish his father. So they performed all
        that the king commanded. And after that God heeded the prayer for the land.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'When the Philistines were at war again with Israel, David and his
        servants with him went down and fought against the Philistines; and David
        grew faint. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then Ishbi-Benob, who was one of the sons of the giant, the weight
        of whose bronze spear was three hundred shekels, who was bearing a new sword,
        thought he could kill David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "But Abishai the son of Zeruiah came to his aid, and struck the Philistine
        and killed him. Then the men of David swore to him, saying, \u201CYou shall
        go out no more with us to battle, lest you quench the lamp of Israel.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Now it happened afterward that there was again a battle with the
        Philistines at Gob. Then Sibbechai the Hushathite killed Saph, who was one
        of the sons of the giant. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Again there was war at Gob with the Philistines, where Elhanan the
        son of Jaare-Oregim the Bethlehemite killed the  brother  of Goliath the
        Gittite, the shaft of whose spear was like a weaver\u2019s beam."
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Yet again there was war at Gath, where there was a man of great stature,
        who had six fingers on each hand and six toes on each foot, twenty-four in
        number; and he also was born to the giant. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "So when he defied Israel, Jonathan the son of Shimea, David\u2019s
        brother, killed him."
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: These four were born to the giant in Gath, and fell by the hand of
        David and by the hand of his servants.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Praise for God\u2019s Deliverance"
      title: "Praise for God\u2019s Deliverance"
      number: 1
      content: 'Then David spoke to the Lord the words of this song, on the day when
        the Lord had delivered him from the hand of all his enemies, and from the
        hand of Saul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And he said:\u201CThe Lord  is my rock and my fortress and my deliverer;"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: The God of my strength, in whom I will trust;My shield and the horn
        of my salvation,My stronghold and my refuge;My Savior, You save me from violence.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: I will call upon the Lord, who  is  worthy to be praised;So shall
        I be saved from my enemies.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CWhen the waves of death surrounded me,The floods of ungodliness
        made me afraid."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: The sorrows of Sheol surrounded me;The snares of death confronted
        me.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: In my distress I called upon the Lord,And cried out to my God;He heard
        my voice from His temple,And my cry entered His ears.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CThen the earth shook and trembled;The foundations of heaven
        quaked and were shaken,Because He was angry."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Smoke went up from His nostrils,And devouring fire from His mouth;Coals
        were kindled by it.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: He bowed the heavens also, and came downWith darkness under His feet.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: He rode upon a cherub, and flew;And He was seen upon the wings of
        the wind.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: He made darkness canopies around Him,Dark waters and thick clouds
        of the skies.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: From the brightness before HimCoals of fire were kindled.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CThe Lord  thundered from heaven,And the Most High uttered His
        voice."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: He sent out arrows and scattered them;Lightning bolts, and He vanquished
        them.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: Then the channels of the sea were seen,The foundations of the world
        were uncovered,At the rebuke of the Lord,At the blast of the breath of His
        nostrils.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CHe sent from above, He took me,He drew me out of many waters."
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: He delivered me from my strong enemy,From those who hated me;For they
        were too strong for me.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: They confronted me in the day of my calamity,But the Lord was my support.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: He also brought me out into a broad place;He delivered me because
        He delighted in me.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CThe  Lord rewarded me according to my righteousness;According
        to the cleanness of my handsHe has recompensed me."
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: For I have kept the ways of the Lord,And have not wickedly departed
        from my God.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: For all His judgments were before me;And as  for His statutes, I did
        not depart from them.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: I was also blameless before Him,And I kept myself from my iniquity.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: Therefore the Lord has recompensed me according to my righteousness,According
        to my cleanness in His eyes.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CWith the merciful You will show Yourself merciful;With a blameless
        man You will show Yourself blameless;"
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: With the pure You will show Yourself pure;And with the devious You
        will show Yourself shrewd.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: You will save the humble people;But Your eyes are on the haughty,
        that You may bring them down.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u201CFor You are my lamp, O Lord;The Lord shall enlighten my darkness."
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: For by You I can run against a troop;By my God I can leap over a wall.
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: As  for God, His way is perfect;The word of the Lord  is proven;He
        is a shield to all who trust in Him.
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "\u201CFor who is God, except the Lord?And who is a rock, except our
        God?"
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: God is my strength and power,And He makes my way perfect.
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: He makes my feet like the feet of deer,And sets me on my high places.
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: He teaches my hands to make war,So that my arms can bend a bow of
        bronze.
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "\u201CYou have also given me the shield of Your salvation;Your gentleness
        has made me great."
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: You enlarged my path under me;So my feet did not slip.
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "\u201CI have pursued my enemies and destroyed them;Neither did I
        turn back again till they were destroyed."
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: And I have destroyed them and wounded them,So that they could not
        rise;They have fallen under my feet.
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: For You have armed me with strength for the battle;You have subdued
        under me those who rose against me.
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: You have also given me the necks of my enemies,So that I destroyed
        those who hated me.
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: They looked, but there  was none to save;Even  to the Lord, but He
        did not answer them.
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: Then I beat them as fine as the dust of the earth;I trod them like
        dirt in the streets,And I spread them out.
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "\u201CYou have also delivered me from the strivings of my people;You
        have kept me as the head of the nations.A people I have not known shall serve
        me."
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: The foreigners submit to me;As soon as they hear, they obey me.
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: The foreigners fade away,And come frightened from their hideouts.
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "\u201CThe Lord lives!Blessed be my Rock!Let God be exalted,The Rock
        of my salvation!"
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: It  is God who avenges me,And subdues the peoples under me;
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: He delivers me from my enemies.You also lift me up above those who
        rise against me;You have delivered me from the violent man.
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: Therefore I will give thanks to You, O Lord, among the Gentiles,And
        sing praises to Your name.
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: "\u201CHe is the tower of salvation to His king,And shows mercy to
        His anointed,To David and his descendants forevermore.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: David\u2019s Last Words"
      title: "David\u2019s Last Words"
      number: 1
      content: 'Now these are the last words of David.Thus says David the son of
        Jesse;Thus says the man raised up on high,The anointed of the God of Jacob,And
        the sweet psalmist of Israel:'
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CThe Spirit of the Lord spoke by me,And His word was on my tongue."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "The God of Israel said,The Rock of Israel spoke to me:\u2018He who
        rules over men must  be just,Ruling in the fear of God."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And he  shall  be like the light of the morning when the sun rises,A
        morning without clouds,Like the tender grass springing out of the earth,By
        clear shining after rain.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CAlthough my house is not so with God,Yet He has made with me
        an everlasting covenant,Ordered in all things and secure.For this  is all
        my salvation and all my desire;Will He not make it increase?"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: But the  sons of rebellion shall all be as thorns thrust away,Because
        they cannot be taken with hands.
      comments: []
    - name: "7: David\u2019s Mighty Men"
      title: "David\u2019s Mighty Men"
      number: 7
      content: "But the man who touches themMust be armed with iron and the shaft
        of a spear,And they shall be utterly burned with fire in their place.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'These are the names of the mighty men whom David had: Josheb-Basshebeth
        the Tachmonite, chief among the captains. He was called Adino the Eznite,
        because he had killed eight hundred men at one time. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And after him was  Eleazar the son of Dodo, the Ahohite, one of the
        three mighty men with David when they defied the Philistines who were gathered
        there for battle, and the men of Israel had retreated. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'He arose and attacked the Philistines until his hand was weary, and
        his hand stuck to the sword. The Lord brought about a great victory that
        day; and the people returned after him only to plunder. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And after him was  Shammah the son of Agee the Hararite. The Philistines
        had gathered together into a troop where there was a piece of ground full
        of lentils. So the people fled from the Philistines. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: But he stationed himself in the middle of the field, defended it,
        and killed the Philistines. So the Lord brought about a great victory.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then three of the thirty chief men went down at harvest time and
        came to David at the cave of Adullam. And the troop of Philistines encamped
        in the Valley of Rephaim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'David was then in the stronghold, and the garrison of the Philistines
        was then in Bethlehem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And David said with longing, \u201COh, that someone would give me
        a drink of the water from the well of Bethlehem, which is by the gate!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So the three mighty men broke through the camp of the Philistines,
        drew water from the well of Bethlehem that was by the gate, and took it and
        brought it to David. Nevertheless he would not drink it, but poured it out
        to the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And he said, \u201CFar be it from me, O Lord, that I should do this!
        Is this  not  the blood of the men who went in jeopardy  of their lives?\u201D
        Therefore he would not drink it.These things were done by the three mighty
        men."
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Now Abishai the brother of Joab, the son of Zeruiah, was chief of
        another three. He lifted his spear against three hundred men, killed them,
        and won a name among these three. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: Was he not the most honored of three? Therefore he became their captain.
        However, he did not attain to the first three.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Benaiah was the son of Jehoiada, the son of a valiant man from Kabzeel,
        who had done many deeds. He had killed two lion-like heroes of Moab. He also
        had gone down and killed a lion in the midst of a pit on a snowy day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And he killed an Egyptian, a spectacular man. The Egyptian had a
        spear in his hand; so he went down to him with a staff, wrested the spear
        out of the Egyptian\u2019s hand, and killed him with his own spear. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'These things Benaiah the son of Jehoiada did, and won a name among
        three mighty men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: He was more honored than the thirty, but he did not attain to the
        first three. And David appointed him over his guard.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Asahel the brother of Joab was one of the thirty; Elhanan the son
        of Dodo of Bethlehem, '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Shammah the Harodite, Elika the Harodite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Helez the Paltite, Ira the son of Ikkesh the Tekoite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Abiezer the Anathothite, Mebunnai the Hushathite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Zalmon the Ahohite, Maharai the Netophathite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Heleb the son of Baanah (the Netophathite), Ittai the son of Ribai
        from Gibeah of the children of Benjamin, '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Benaiah a Pirathonite, Hiddai from the brooks of Gaash, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Abi-Albon the Arbathite, Azmaveth the Barhumite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Eliahba the Shaalbonite (of the sons of Jashen), Jonathan, '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Shammah the Hararite, Ahiam the son of Sharar the Hararite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Eliphelet the son of Ahasbai, the son of the Maachathite, Eliam the
        son of Ahithophel the Gilonite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Hezrai the Carmelite, Paarai the Arbite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Igal the son of Nathan of Zobah, Bani the Gadite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Zelek the Ammonite, Naharai the Beerothite (armorbearer of Joab the
        son of Zeruiah), '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'Ira the Ithrite, Gareb the Ithrite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'and  Uriah the Hittite: thirty-seven in all.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: David\u2019s Census of Israel and Judah"
      title: "David\u2019s Census of Israel and Judah"
      number: 1
      content: "Again the anger of the Lord was aroused against Israel, and He moved
        David against them to say, \u201CGo, number Israel and Judah.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "So the king said to Joab the commander of the army who was with him,
        \u201CNow go throughout all the tribes of Israel, from Dan to Beersheba,
        and count the people, that I may know the number of the people.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And Joab said to the king, \u201CNow may the Lord your God add to
        the people a hundred times more than there are, and may the eyes of my lord
        the king see it. But why does my lord the king desire this thing?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Nevertheless the king\u2019s word prevailed against Joab and against
        the captains of the army. Therefore Joab and the captains of the army went
        out from the presence of the king to count the people of Israel."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And they crossed over the Jordan and camped in Aroer, on the right
        side of the town which is in the midst of the ravine of Gad, and toward Jazer. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then they came to Gilead and to the land of Tahtim Hodshi; they came
        to Dan Jaan and around to Sidon; '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'and they came to the stronghold of Tyre and to all the cities of
        the Hivites and the Canaanites. Then they went out to South Judah as  far 
        as Beersheba. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So when they had gone through all the land, they came to Jerusalem
        at the end of nine months and twenty days. '
      comments: []
    - name: "9: The Judgment on David\u2019s Sin"
      title: "The Judgment on David\u2019s Sin"
      number: 9
      content: Then Joab gave the sum of the number of the people to the king. And
        there were in Israel eight hundred thousand valiant men who drew the sword,
        and the men of Judah were five hundred thousand men.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And David\u2019s heart condemned him after he had numbered the people.
        So David said to the Lord, \u201CI have sinned greatly in what I have done;
        but now, I pray, O Lord, take away the iniquity of Your servant, for I have
        done very foolishly.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Now when David arose in the morning, the word of the Lord came to
        the prophet Gad, David\u2019s seer, saying, "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CGo and tell David, \u2018Thus says the Lord: \u201CI offer
        you three things; choose one of them for yourself, that I may do it to you.\u201D
        \u2019 \u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "So Gad came to David and told him; and he said to him, \u201CShall
        seven years of famine come to you in your land? Or shall you flee three months
        before your enemies, while they pursue you? Or shall there be three days\u2019
        plague in your land? Now consider and see what answer I should take back
        to Him who sent me.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And David said to Gad, \u201CI am in great distress. Please let us
        fall into the hand of the Lord, for His mercies are great; but do not let
        me fall into the hand of man.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So the Lord sent a plague upon Israel from the morning till the appointed
        time. From Dan to Beersheba seventy thousand men of the people died. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And when the angel stretched out His hand over Jerusalem to destroy
        it, the Lord relented from the destruction, and said to the angel who was
        destroying the people, \u201CIt is enough; now restrain your hand.\u201D
        And the angel of the Lord was by the threshing floor of Araunah the Jebusite."
      comments: []
    - name: '17: The Altar on the Threshing Floor'
      title: The Altar on the Threshing Floor
      number: 17
      content: "Then David spoke to the Lord when he saw the angel who was striking
        the people, and said, \u201CSurely I have sinned, and I have done wickedly;
        but these sheep, what have they done? Let Your hand, I pray, be against me
        and against my father\u2019s house.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And Gad came that day to David and said to him, \u201CGo up, erect
        an altar to the Lord on the threshing floor of Araunah the Jebusite.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'So David, according to the word of Gad, went up as the Lord commanded. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Now Araunah looked, and saw the king and his servants coming toward
        him. So Araunah went out and bowed before the king with his face to the ground.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then Araunah said, \u201CWhy has my lord the king come to his servant?\u201DAnd
        David said, \u201CTo buy the threshing floor from you, to build an altar
        to the Lord, that the plague may be withdrawn from the people.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Now Araunah said to David, \u201CLet my lord the king take and offer
        up whatever seems good to him. Look, here  are oxen for burnt sacrifice,
        and threshing implements and the yokes of the oxen for wood. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "All these, O king, Araunah has given to the king.\u201DAnd Araunah
        said to the king, \u201CMay the Lord your God accept you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Then the king said to Araunah, \u201CNo, but I will surely buy it
        from you for a price; nor will I offer burnt offerings to the Lord my God
        with that which costs me nothing.\u201D So David bought the threshing floor
        and the oxen for fifty shekels of silver. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: And David built there an altar to the Lord, and offered burnt offerings
        and peace offerings. So the Lord heeded the prayers for the land, and the
        plague was withdrawn from Israel.
      comments: []
